You may need to make that move yourself. They will absolutely take advantage of you if you're doing good work - hell, even if they offer you a salary(!), they'll continue to try to take advantage of you. Tell you're boss you'd like to be employed full or part-time, whatever they need. In the meantime, try to shop for prospective employers, tout your experience (it IS experience), get someone you've worked with to offer him/herself as a contact reference, maybe even your boss. There's no point in having skill or experience in a trade or discipline if you're doing it for free. Never do it for free; internships are for building contacts and experience that you can use to get employed later. And don't let a job requiring [x] years of experience intimidate you, always contact prospective employers and find out from someone in HR/management if they will or won't hire you.
